{
  "texts": [
    "with 100 μg/mL of ampicillin (TB-amp) per well in 96-well deep-well plates.",
    "These expression cultures were initially incubated at 37 °C and 220 rpm for 2.5 h, at which point they were allowed to sit at room temperature for 30 min.",
    "Expression of proteins was induced with isopropyl-β-D-thiogalactoside (IPTG) and cellular heme production was increased with 5-aminolevulinic acid (ALA).",
    "An induction mixture containing IPTG and ALA in TB-amp (50 μL) was added to each well such that the final concentrations of IPTG and ALA were 0.5 mM and 1.0 mM, respectively.",
    "The total culture volumes were 1 mL."
  ]
}